          <div class="date-outer">
        
<h2 class='date-header'><span>Sunday, 9 January 2011</span></h2>

          <div class="date-posts">
        
<div class='post-outer'>
<div class='post hentry'>
<a name='4080355786679672659'></a>
<h3 class='post-title entry-title'>
<a href='http://www.kuriositas.com/2011/01/en-v-is-this-car-of-future.html'>The EN-V &#8211; Is this the Car of the Future?</a>
</h3>
<div class='post-header'>
<div class='post-header-line-1'></div>
</div>
<div class='post-body entry-content'>
<div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/24641875@N07/4458575069/" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" height="426" src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_-zOrAL1V5Jg/TSoKyO20koI/AAAAAAAAJDw/gSvO_lJN9s8/s640/ENV+Electric-Networked+Vehicle+GM+General+Motors+Unveiled+1.jpg" width="640" /></a></div><div style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/24641875@N07/4458575069/"><span style="font-size: xx-small;">Image Credit Flickr User Segway Social2</span></a></div>There is an old joke about small cars which has travelled (changed to various manufacturers and models according to geography) around the world.&nbsp; The joke goes that a small animal, let&#8217;s say a rabit, in involved in a collision with one of them.&nbsp; The punch line goes that the rabbit gets up, brushes himself down and goes about his business: the car is a write off.<br />
<br />
<div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/24641875@N07/4459354228/" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" height="426" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_-zOrAL1V5Jg/TSoLQSkg2eI/AAAAAAAAJD0/dXflcag5DoQ/s640/ENV+Electric-Networked+Vehicle+GM+General+Motors+Unveiled+2.jpg" width="640" /></a></div><div style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/24641875@N07/4459354228/"><span style="font-size: xx-small;">Image Credit Flickr User Segway Social2</span></a></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/24641875@N07/4458575223/" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" height="426" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_-zOrAL1V5Jg/TSoLz_YHkiI/AAAAAAAAJD4/C6PzOo5sKpw/s640/ENV+Electric-Networked+Vehicle+GM+General+Motors+Unveiled+3.jpg" width="640" /></a></div><div style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/24641875@N07/4458575223/"><span style="font-size: xx-small;">Image Credit Flickr User Segwaysocial2</span></a></div>Perhaps the same joke will be levelled at the EN-V (or the Electric-Networked Vehicle) if you prefer the longer version. You can certainly take a second or two as time out to shudder at the prospect of being in one of these wedges between two pickup trucks.&nbsp; However, that aside, the EN-V may well revolutionise the way we travel, particularly in urban areas.<br />
<br />
<center><img height="960" src="http://farm5.static.flickr.com/4031/4458575547_455a512407_b.jpg" width="640" /></center><div style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/24641875@N07/4458575547/"><span style="font-size: xx-small;">Image Credit Flickr User Segway Social2</span></a></div>For starters the two-seater car has twin electric motors and something called dynamic stabilization technology.&nbsp; This allows them to turn on a penny.&nbsp; They can also be charged up from a conventional wall outlet.&nbsp; Take in to account their integrated GPS system which allows them to operate autonomously and if they don&#8217;t attract the motoring fan they may just be a magnet for those not too shy to reveal their inner geek.<br />
<br />
<center><img height="960" src="http://farm6.static.flickr.com/5041/5334337092_f1272cfc36_b.jpg" width="640" /></center><div style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/etcusc/5334337092/"><span style="font-size: xx-small;">Image Credit Flickr User ETC@USC</span></a></div>The EN-V may offer the solution for which drivers have been waiting for decades.&nbsp; If adopted, lack of parking and traffic jams could become a thing of the past.&nbsp; Not only that, its design takes in to account three things which pre-occupy many drivers; affordability, how much energy it consumes and what damage the vehicle might do to our already fragile environment.<br />
<br />
<div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/etcusc/5333721507/in/photostream/" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" height="426" src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_-zOrAL1V5Jg/TSoNr5xkrTI/AAAAAAAAJD8/SsckCmYwVaU/s640/ENV+Electric-Networked+Vehicle+GM+General+Motors+Unveiled+4.jpg" width="640" /></a></div><div style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/etcusc/5333721507/in/photostream/"><span style="font-size: xx-small;">Image Credit Flickr User ETC@USC</span></a></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/etcusc/5333721671/in/photostream/" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" height="426" src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_-zOrAL1V5Jg/TSoOHrV1SVI/AAAAAAAAJEA/HmkE8pj549Q/s640/ENV+Electric-Networked+Vehicle+GM+General+Motors+Unveiled+5.jpg" width="640" /></a></div><div style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/etcusc/5333721671/in/photostream/"><span style="font-size: xx-small;">Image Credit Flickr User ETC@USC</span></a></div>The GM version of the EN-V can rotate through 360 degrees and be driven, if necessary, without a driver.&nbsp; It will keep running for around 25 miles and goes up to 25 miles per hour.&nbsp; This is expected to improve, however.&nbsp; When it comes to being remote controlled, however, this would mean that cities would have to create areas that would be only used by EN-Vs, something we see in science fiction movies but is possibly unlikely in our lifetimes.<br />
<br />
<center><img height="960" src="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2785/4458574801_b697d68ed1_b.jpg" width="639" /></center><div style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/24641875@N07/4458574801/"><span style="font-size: xx-small;">Image Credit Flickr User Segway Social2</span></a></div>Yet could it be that GM &#8211; of all possible companies &#8211; might be able to persuade the gas guzzling public to go electric.&nbsp; Certainly the three two seater models which have recently made their debut are turning heads, both in the design and the driving world.<br />
<br />
<div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/24641875@N07/4459354262/" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" height="426" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_-zOrAL1V5Jg/TSoO--hqqDI/AAAAAAAAJEE/ZJKC-reDdeU/s640/ENV+Electric-Networked+Vehicle+GM+General+Motors+Unveiled+6.jpg" width="640" /></a></div><div style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/24641875@N07/4459354262/"><span style="font-size: xx-small;">Image Credit Flickr User Segway Social2</span></a></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/24641875@N07/4458573367/" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" height="426" src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_-zOrAL1V5Jg/TSoPTDWKxEI/AAAAAAAAJEI/z3ZLAX79Ycs/s640/ENV+Electric-Networked+Vehicle+GM+General+Motors+Unveiled+7.jpg" width="640" /></a></div><div style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/24641875@N07/4458573367/"><span style="font-size: xx-small;">Image Credit Flickr User Segway Social2</span></a></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"></div><div style="text-align: center;"><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/24641875@N07/4459354314/" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" height="426" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_-zOrAL1V5Jg/TSoP7G0_GcI/AAAAAAAAJEQ/5itXGU4egCE/s640/ENV+Electric-Networked+Vehicle+GM+General+Motors+Unveiled+8.jpg" width="640" /></a></div><a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/24641875@N07/4459354314/"><span style="font-size: xx-small;">Image Credit Flickr User Segway Social12</span></a></div>There are currently three models, Laugh, Pride and and Magic.&nbsp; All three names could do with a little work, to be perfectly honest.In our pictures, the red EN-V is <i>Pride </i>(not to be confused with one of the seven deadly sins or an annual LGBT event) and <i>Magic</i> is the black model.&nbsp; <i>Laugh </i>(possibly in <i>you're having a...)</i> is the blue one.<br />
<div style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: xx-small;"><br />
</span></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/24641875@N07/4458575429/" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" height="426" src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_-zOrAL1V5Jg/TSoQXe9BqSI/AAAAAAAAJEU/hLoUear54ME/s640/ENV+Electric-Networked+Vehicle+GM+General+Motors+Unveiled+9.jpg" width="640" /></a></div><div style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: xx-small;"> </span></div><div style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/24641875@N07/4458575429/"><span style="font-size: xx-small;">Image Credit Flickr User Segway Social2</span></a></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/24641875@N07/4459355088/" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" height="480" src="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_-zOrAL1V5Jg/TSoRcumAA2I/AAAAAAAAJEY/z6XGBTtBIjM/s640/ENV+Electric-Networked+Vehicle+GM+General+Motors+Unveiled+10.jpg" width="640" /></a></div><div style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/24641875@N07/4459355088/"><span style="font-size: xx-small;">Image Credit Flickr User Segwaysocial2</span></a></div>The design is one of those which people will either love or hate.&nbsp; Brightly colored and worryingly reminiscent of the a motorcycle helmet, it will take time to convince many people that the EN-V is the way forward &#8211; if indeed they can ever be convinced.<br />
<br />
<center><img height="960" src="http://farm5.static.flickr.com/4007/4459355088_60f03b6f3f_b.jpg" width="640" /></center><div style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/24641875@N07/4459355088/"><span style="font-size: xx-small;">Image Credit Flickr User Segway Social2</span></a></div>Please don&#8217;t get too excited just yet, however. The shame of all of this is that there is no timeframe for when the EN-V will be available to purchase.
<div style='clear: both;'></div>
</div>
<div class='post-footer'>
